Someone can correct me if I am wrong, but I believe it has been 
around for awhile and received notoriety from Ghost Hunters episodes 
last year.  The distributor out of Florida marked them way up on eBay 
and limited distribution to himself until the sensation ceased and he 
had made a pretty penny.  It&#39;s an old unit to boot.  It is nothing 
more than an EMF meter with sensitivity lights in place of a meter 
from what I understand.  So if one sees a spike in EMF waves, some 
ghost hunters ask a question in the same area and watch for a spike 
as &quot;Yes.&quot;  No spike as &quot;No.  I believe this is what I heard, but I 
may stand to be corrected if in error.

LC

